Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '162. Name Antipatros. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roan Museum, ABC 0062.09.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (38)
